Lake Cunningham has four entry points to the park. All entrances feature parking and convenient access to the multi-purpose concrete trail. Entrances are open year-round during park hours of 5:00am-11:00pm. The Campground entrance is open seasonally, typically May-October. Entrance #1 - Marina 8965 State Street, Omaha, NE 68122 Our most popular entrance which features the trademark “lighthouse” the Lake C brand is built around. Entrance #1 offers many amenities for park-goers such as: Boat ramp/boat parking Water equipment loading & unloading zone Access to C Store concessions (Fri & Sat 3-8pm East pedestrian bridge Access to the campground playground Restroom facility Marina Lighthouse Disc golf course Fishing pier Entrance #2 - Overlook 9195 State Street, Omaha, NE 68122 Entrance #2 features a beautiful “overlook” of Lake C. In our opinion, the best view of the lake can be accessed from this entrance. Some of the other amenities this entrance offers are: 1 Small shelter Grill Enclosed portable restroom Easy access to the trail View of the dam and lake Entrance #3 - Garvin Rd & N 96th St 9600 Garvin Road, Omaha, NE 68122 Entrance #3 offers many great amenities and is most known for the accessible kayak launch and the beautiful shelter views! Below you’ll find more amenities you’re looking for! Handicap accessible kayak launch Horseshoes (Dave Van Metre Court) Bocce ball court (Dave Van Metre Court) Fishing dock 2 Small picnic shelters 1 Large picnic shelter Grills Enclosed portable restroom Entrance #4 - North Trailhead Access 9307 Bennington Road, Omaha, NE 68122 Entrance #4 provides convenient access to the north side of Lake Cunningham, making it ideal for those looking to explore the trails, enjoy fishing, or take in a stunning view of the lake from a unique perspective. Trailhead Access Handicap Accessible Fishing Access Historical Markers Campground Entrance 8305 Rainwood Road, Omaha, NE 68122 Open during the campground season, this entrance offers access to our campground patrons. The Campground Entrance features the following: Dump station Freshwater fill station Access to the East C Campground Access to the West C Campground C Store Concessions in the East C (Fri & Sat 3-8pm) Playground Archery Range Entrance 9100 Pawnee Road, Omaha, NE 68122 Featuring a stationary archery range with nine targets and scenic range with eleven 3D lanes. The Lake C archery range is open year-round to the public. Please make sure to check out when archery tournaments take place throughout the year on our events page. 9 target stationary range 11 lane 3D range Open year-round for public use Designated for archer use only Equestrian & Multipurpose Nature Trail Entrance North 96th & HWY 36, Omaha, NE 68122 Lake Cunningham is home to nearly 20 miles of beautiful multipurpose nature trails north of HWY 36 and 96th Street. The trails are open year-round for multipurpose use. We do not offer horse rental services. Equestrian & multipurpose nature trails 19 miles of total trail Parking lot suitable for horse trailers Open year-round for public use Contact Information Office Hours: Monday-Friday 9:00am-4:30pm 8965 State St, Omaha, NE 68122 531-201-5754 explorethec@lakecunningham.org Have Questions? About us 9Trees was formed in 2018 by Michael Cunningham, an experienced habitat and business manager. In 2019 he was joined by Ash Kent, an experienced countryside and habitat manager. We now have a team of amazing volunteers who’ve joined us. Our vision is to tackle climate change by restoring new woodland habitats, promote biodiversity, create jobs within the countryside sector and connect more people to nature. We are a Community Interest Company, ploughing any profits back into good schemes, training and education. Why we are different At 9Trees we plant in the UK, we look after your trees, and we keep you up-to-date with their progress. We continue to look after your trees, so they store as much carbon as possible. Our specialist knowledge in conservation means we’re able to create woodlands that support local wildlife and improve biodiversity. We work with local authorities and organisations to plant on carefully selected land, not destroying vital flower meadows, peat land or other Special Sites of Scientific Interest. We work directly within communities, using local specialists to give your trees the very best start in life. All our trees are native and grown in the UK, with the species of tree chosen to suit each site. Some landowners will even allow you to visit your trees! Meet the Team 9Trees is powered by a dedicated team of individuals working together to combat climate change. Featured Jo Bradley Jo lives in Lancashire and works in stormwater management. She has had a long career in all aspects of pollution control and environment protection, but she recognises the risks of climate change and she enjoys supporting 9Trees so that she can contribute to the creation of new broadleaved woodlands that provide safe habitats for many birds and woodland creatures. Find out more at Jo's LinkedIn page . Bobo Tang Bobo is a web developer and content creator who is passionate about using her skills to make a positive impact on the environment. She believes that technology could be used to promote sustainability and help create a better world. She wants to apply her skills to help 9Trees promote environmental sustainability and make their website more effective and user-friendly. Hannah Davies Hannah is a Creative Marketing Consultant who studied Journalism, Media & Cultural Criticism at Cardiff University. With a background in the creative and cultural industries, she is driven by her passion for making the world a more colourful place, both in nature and our community cultures. At 9Trees, Hannah is utilising her expertise to develop effective marketing and communications strategies that promote the company's commitment to sustainability and environmental responsibility. Eirini Chatzidaki Eirini is an avid hiker who is dedicated to raising awareness about the impact of climate change on the natural world and encouraging companies to play a role in its preservation and protection. With previous experience as a recruiter and a Master's degree in Environmental Sustainability from The University of Edinburgh, she now serves as a business development manager, expanding the network of supporters and driving the growth of tree planting initiatives to maximise their positive impact. Tina Rana Tina has always had an affinity towards the environment and felt great stewardship in regards to its sustainability. Resulting in her acquiring a bachelors in Ecology and Conservation at Brighton University in 2023. At 9Trees, Tina works as a Landowner Survey Assistant, writing desk-based assessments on various proposed sites to determine their compatibility with our planting. She also assists with landowner liaison and coordination. Tara El Kashef Tara is a Master’s student in Anthropology, Environment and Development at UCL with an interest in urban sustainability practices. She believes businesses should play a more active role in natural resource conservation and is enthusiastic to promote this through 9Trees. Tara is one of our volunteer ambassadors, promoting our mission to local venues and public figures who share our values. Volunteering and pro-bono opportunities We have a wide range of volunteering and pro-bono opportunities on offer, ranging from business and social media management to landowner support and tree care. About us - PARK Consulting Academy Coaching Connections Close menu 01 Consulting Building and scaling capabilities 02 Academy Growing tomorrow's leaders 03 Coaching Guiding teams & individuals 04 Connections Connecting peers across the globe Menu About us What’s on News + Opinion Livebook Contact © Park 2025 Privacy Policy About us / Since 1998, PARK has been building and scaling design capabilities for the organisations and people that want to create a better tomorrow. PARK Values Empathetic We know that empathy and understanding is at the heart of good design, good relationships and good business. Challenging We don't shy away from challenging the status quo to maximise value for everyone involved. Partnering We work with clients, not for clients. Co-creation and rapid iteration leads to the best results. Personalised We treat every challenge as unique. We're not a transactional, cookie-cutter consultancy. Accountable We feel a sense of ownership alongside our clients. We see every detail right through to the end. PARK History PARK Consulting was founded in 1998 by Tim Selders and Frans Joziasse. Both experienced designers, they'd both become increasingly frustrated with the disconnect between design and business. They saw an opportunity to bridge the gap by creating a unique proposition that focused on helping leaders to establish design as a business enabler and growth driver. PARK Consulting was born and was an immediate success, finding its niche with early clients including Sony, Kia/Hyundai, LEGO, and HP. Since those early days, the role of Design Leadership has significantly evolved. Today, enabling and driving business growth is just the start. Leaders of design now need to build bridges across touchpoints and functions, develop next-generation capabilities, act as a catalyst for business-wide change and, of course, always do more with less. As the landscape for design leadership has evolved, so has PARK. Regularly viewed as a thought leader in the industry, PARK Consulting has now partnered with over 300 different clients. In 2013, to complement PARK's consulting services, Grow (now known as PARK Academy) was established with the aim of 'empowering design leaders' through education. We're very proud that PARK Academy has since had a positive impact on the careers of more than 2000 Design Management and Design Leadership students across Europe and the USA. In 2023 PARK celebrates its 25th anniversary as the business ownership transitions to James Hall and Andy Sharpe, with Frans Joziasse continuing as an integral part of the leadership team until 2028. We’re also consolidating the business into the 4 services – Consulting, Academy, Coaching and Connections. Looking back, it's been a wonderful 25 years, and we look forward to more of the same. Why 'PARK'? The name PARK stems from the East Gardens of the Imperial Palace near the Marunouchi Business District in Tokyo. A park in which co-founder Frans would spend his lunch break whilst visiting Japan during the 1990s. This park is where locals go to reflect, relax and dream – just a few of the things that we try to facilitate here at PARK. Unique consulting clients partnered since 1998 + Graduates from our PARK Academy since 2013 + Design Managers/Leaders coached annually Design leaders have now participated in a PARK cross-company retreat Timeline PARK is founded PARK Consulting is founded by Frans Joziasse and Tim Selders in the Netherlands and Germany. First client project PARK's first client is Sony Personal Audio Europe, working on their European Design Strategy. Consulting team expands PARK employs its first full-time consultants - Professor Aart van Bezooyen and Assistant Professor Jasper van Kuijk. Growth in adversity PARK sees significant success amidst a global financial crisis, and builds long-term relationships with BMW, LEGO, PANalytical, Grundfos and Reckitt Benckiser. PARK keeps growing PARK expands team to 12 consultants from 8 different nationalities. Grow Academy established Grow, a spin-off of the LEGO Design Academy is founded with the aim of ‘empowering design leaders’ through education in the areas of Design Management and Design Leadership. PARK USA founded PARK goes stateside with the launch of PARK and Grow USA, led by Jay Peters. Design for Humanity launches PARK establishes the Design for Humanity movement, gathering 30 leaders of design in Hamburg for the inaugural D4H retreat. Livebook 2.0 PARK launches a major upgrade of the digital platform used to support the delivery of Grow programmes. PARK hits 2000 graduations Grow celebrates its 2000th student graduation with the delivery of cross-company and in-company programmes in the USA, UK, Germany, Norway, Ireland, Estonia and Slovenia. 25 year anniversary PARK celebrates its 25th anniversary. Company ownership transitions from Frans Joziasse to James Hall and Andy Sharpe. Re-brand and simplification PARK simplifies its service offer and re-brands every touchpoint across the business. Grow becomes PARK Academy. 1998 Meet the team Andy Sharpe Company Director Andy Sharpe Company Director sharpe@park.bz Linkedin Andy is a Senior Consultant and Director at PARK. Originally trained as a product designer, he spent 17 years client-side at Unilever, working in Design Management and Leadership roles in both the UK and USA. After many years as a client of PARK, in 2018 he jumped the fence and in 2023 became a co-owner alongside James Hall. Andy underpins everything he does with a belief – that human progress means keeping things simple. Brian Gillespie Senior Tutor, PARK Academy Brian Gillespie Senior Tutor, PARK Academy gillespie@park.bz Linkedin With his extensive experience in strategic design and managing human-centred, digital products and services, Brian’s end-goal is always about the benefits of great design. He’s collaborated with teams from a diverse range of global organisations, including Audi, Philips, Vanguard, Adidas, Fidelity and JP Morgan Chase. He’s also a coach on our PARK Academy program. Brian holds an MBA in Design Management and serves on the leadership team of the Service Design Network. Carola Boogerd Business Manager Carola Boogerd Business Manager boogerd@park.bz Linkedin In 2008 Carola joined PARK as our office manager. Since then, her role has expanded to cover management of business operations. With her enthusiastic, can-do attitude and an aptitude for listening, she’s facilitated many of our Design Leadership programs, ensuring everything runs smoothly. Denisse Bronsoiler Consultant & Project Manager USA Denisse Bronsoiler Consultant & Project Manager USA bronsoiler@park.bz Linkedin Denisse joined PARK in 2018. Specialising in managing digital projects, Denisse has been responsible for Livebook – our very own e-learning platform. With a background not only in Design Management and Interactive Design, but also finance, Denisse has a creative mind as well as a business one. Consulting clients in strategy and branding, her experience also makes her perfectly suited to our Design Leadership education programs. Frans Joziasse Founding Director Frans Joziasse Founding Director joziasse@park.bz Linkedin As a co-founder of PARK and leader of the organisation over the last 25 years, Frans is proud of the strong vision he has instilled and the inspiring team he has built. With a firm belief in the power of design, he relishes watching his clients reach their full potential and seeing what impact strong leadership can have both on business and the planet. Hans Henrik Ruus Business Visualiser Hans Henrik Ruus Business Visualiser ruus@park.bz Linkedin Hans is a skilled artist and visualiser with a background in advertising. For over a decade, he created campaigns for both Danish and international clients. Hans has the rare ability to draw ‘fluently’, capturing and visualising any idea on the fly during meetings and workshops. Originally working for PARK for many years as a freelancer, Hans joined the team in 2021. James Hall Company Director James Hall Company Director hall@park.bz Linkedin James joined PARK in 2013 following an extensive career in product design at both LEGO and Hasbro. Here he honed his skills in design leadership – directing, managing and launching multiple consumer products worldwide. Today, James not only teaches the Academy programs, but is also a senior consultant and Company Director at PARK. From embracing new design leadership techniques to helping people discover new ways to think, James’ raison d’être is to help his clients reach their goals. Jay Peters Partner, USA Jay Peters Partner, USA peters@park.bz Linkedin Jay is a well-versed design and innovation leadership consultant. With 25 years’ experience in business, brand and design, he’s been coaching PARK clients since 2010 – transforming their businesses, maximising value across the triple bottom line and using collaboration, co-creation and communication to set them up for long term success. Stephan Clambaneva Managing Director, USA Stephan Clambaneva Managing Director, USA clambaneva@park.bz Linkedin At PARK Stephan leads projects that transform our clients’ businesses with innovation and design excellence. He also tutors the Design Leadership Academy. Outside of PARK, Stephan serves on the board of directors of the Industrial Designers Society of America and leads their Special Interest section, ensuring a sustainable future. He also regularly writes articles for Innovation magazine, mentors start-ups and guides the NY Design Week Festival as part of the NYCxDesign Advisory Committee. Stay connected Sign up to the PARK newsletter for our latest insights, news, invitations and events.                                     32653-1603 About Visit Natural North Florida Formed in 1993, Visit Natural North Florida (aka The Original Florida Tourism Task Force) is a governmental entity formed through an interlocal agreement among county governments to promote tourism in north central Florida.  The region encompasses Florida’s Big Bend coastal area, spanning Wakulla County in the west down to Cedar Key/Levy County in the south, east to Gainesville, and north to the Florida-Georgia state line.  The Task Force is a founding partner of the official tourism marketing organization for the state, VISIT FLORIDA.  The mission of Visit Natural North Florida is to promote the natural, historic and cultural attractions of the area in order to increase the number of visitors and to extend their stay.  The goal of the organization is to enhance the economy, image and quality of life of the area through expanded revenues and employment opportunities.  At the same time, Visit Natural North Florida encourages the preservation of the resources which bring focus to the area. Lake C slip info ADVENTURE AWAITS YOU Lake Cunningham is a 390-acre lake surrounded by a 1,050-acre park located in north central Omaha, Nebraska. The lake was constructed by the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers for flood control and recreation and opened to the public in 1977. Recreational activities include camping, no-wake boating, fishing, hiking, bicycling, disc golfing, sail boating, and kayaking. North of Highway 36 also offers an archery range and nature trails where you can horseback ride. The vision for Lake Cunningham was built around creating a positive outdoor experience through programs that fulfill the needs of the area and create lasting memories for individuals and families. Park hours, security & entrances Park hours are 5:00am–11:00pm. All park rules are in conjunction with the City of Omaha and can be found on our Park FAQ page. Safety is a top priority at Lake Cunningham. We will have park security patrolling the park seven days a week and there will be 24/7 video surveillance at park entrances and the marina. Gates at entrances #1, #2 and #3 will be closed when the park closes at 11:00pm and will open again at 5:00am when the park opens. Join our List Sign up for the Lake Cunningham mailing list and receive updates on the latest park improvements, news and events. Volunteer with Us At Lake Cunningham, we welcome volunteers and offer a variety of opportunities to put their time and talent to good use in our park. Please note that individuals under the age of 18 must have written consent of the parent or legal guardian before they may volunteer. If you are interested in becoming a volunteer, please contact us at explorethec@lakecunningham.org for more information.
